## Architecture

```mermaid
graph LR
    Camera["📷 Camera Feed"] --> Detection["Obstacle Detection\n(always-on)"]
    Detection --> Risk["RiskEngine + DFPN"]
    Risk --> NavPanel["Navigation Panel (N)"]

    CLI["--floorplan-image\n--floorplan-start\n--floorplan-dest"] --> FPM
    KeyPress["[ key"] --> FPM["FloorplanManager\nbackground thread"]
    FPM --> Pipeline["5-Agent Pipeline\nParser→Graph→Critic→Planner→Safety"]
    Pipeline --> State["ApplicationState\nfloorplan_result"]
    State --> FPPanel["Floorplan Panel (420px)"]
    State --> NavPanel
    FPPanel --> Display["Main Feed Window"]
    NavPanel --> Display
```

---

## How to Use

### Option A — Auto-load at startup
```bash
cd c:\Tim\AIDGPT\AidGPT
python main.py --floorplan-image "alt\dataset\floorplan\images\MP-860-3L.png" ^
               --floorplan-start "Hall" ^
               --floorplan-dest "Kitchen" ^
               --floorplan-provider openai
```
The panel opens immediately showing **RUNNING**, then switches to **DONE ✓** with all nav steps when the pipeline finishes (~30–60s).

### Option B — Toggle panel during live session
Press **`[`** at any time. The panel shows `IDLE — no floorplan loaded` until you restart with the CLI args above.

### Keyboard shortcuts (when panel is visible)
| Key | Action |
|---|---|
| `[` | Open / close the floorplan panel |
| `→` | Advance to next navigation step (also spoken aloud) |
| `←` | Go back to previous step |
| `Enter` | Speak the current step at CRITICAL priority |
| `N` | Toggle the obstacle navigation panel (unchanged) |

---

## What the Floorplan Panel Shows

- **Status badge** — `IDLE` / `RUNNING ⟳` (animated) / `DONE ✓` / `ERROR`
- **Route banner** — "Hall → Kitchen · 12 nodes · 18 edges"
- **Safety badge** — `SAFE (0 hazards)` in green or `UNSAFE (2 hazards)` in orange
- **Current Step card** — action, sensory feedback, heading
- **Step list** — scrollable numbered list, current step highlighted
- **Hazards** — top 3 from safety report
- **Key hints footer**

